    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus containing around 75-100 species of annual, biennial, and perennial herbaceous plants native to temperate and cold regions of Eurasia, Africa, and North America. They have showy solitary flowers  and some species have a milky latex with narcotic properties. Poppies have been cultivated since ca. 5,000 BCE.</Note_Text>
